<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Third to fifth pereiopods (= P 
<number box="[558,600,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
) similar in general shape, robust; P 
<number box="[1032,1045,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
with ischium, merus and carpus unarmed, covered only with small simple setae; propodus about 
<number box="[868,903,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times as long as wide, with straight lateral margins, with three tufts of long simple setae along distoventral margin and one row of simple setae on distal margin; dactylus simple, stout, strongly curved, distally acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Uropods relatively slender, slightly exceeding telson; distolateral tooth and spine subequal in length, moderately strong.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,386,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Colour pattern.</emphasis>
The colour of the 
<typeStatus box="[609,657,368,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
specimens was described as “vert bouteille” = bottle-green (
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Nobili, G. (1906) Mission J. Bonnier er Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 90, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 5." type="journal article" year="1906">
Nobili 
<number box="[151,211,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). To our knowledge, there are no published photographs of 
<taxonomicName box="[879,1013,404,428]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerlachei">
<emphasis box="[879,1013,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. gerlachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Indian Ocean. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce" box="[1287,1436,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Bruce, A. J. (1982) Notes on some Indo-West Pacific Pontoniinae. XL. The rediscovery of Periclimenes lifuensis Borradaile, 1898 (Decapoda, Pontoniine) and the establishment of its systematic position. Crustaceana, 42, 158 - 173." type="journal article" year="1982">
Bruce (
<number box="[1369,1427,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a black-and-white drawing showing the colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[898,1031,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerlachei">
<emphasis box="[898,1031,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. gerlachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Great Barrier Reef, which, however, is characterised by the presence of large dark dorsolateral spots on the first three abdominal somites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,298,512,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ecology.</emphasis>
Appears to be associated with a variety of species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1140,512,536]" class="Anthozoa" family="Acroporidae" genus="Acropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1140,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Acropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dana) (Bruce &amp; Coombes 1995)" authorityName="(Dana) (Bruce &amp; Coombes" authorityYear="1995" class="Anthozoa" family="Acroporidae" genus="Acropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="digitifera">
<emphasis box="[1212,1349,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. digitifera</emphasis>
(Dana) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce" box="[158,435,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Bruce, A. J. &amp; Coombes, K. E. (1995) The palaemonoid shrimp fauna (Crustacea: Decapods: Caridea) of the Cobourg Peninsula, Northern Territory. The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory Museum of Arts and Sciences, 12, 101 - 144." type="journal article" year="1995">
Bruce &amp; Coombes 
<number box="[375,435,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,511,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" box="[197,511,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,355,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus box="[197,256,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Persian Gulf.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,619,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific, ranging from the Red Sea and East Africa to 
<collectingCountry name="French Polynesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[314,378,656,679]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Japan</collectingCountry>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce" box="[449,582,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Bruce, A. J. (1982) Notes on some Indo-West Pacific Pontoniinae. XL. The rediscovery of Periclimenes lifuensis Borradaile, 1898 (Decapoda, Pontoniine) and the establishment of its systematic position. Crustaceana, 42, 158 - 173." type="journal article" year="1982">
Bruce 
<number box="[523,582,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chace" box="[594,833,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. &amp; Bruce, A. J. (1993) The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albatross Philippine Expedition 1907 - 1910, Part 6: Superfamily Palaemonoidea. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 543, 1 - 152." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chace &amp; Bruce 
<number box="[774,833,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; for full list of records see 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[1135,1228,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Li, X. (2000) Catalog of the genera and species of Pontoniinae Kingsley, 1878 (Decapoda, Pontoniinae). Xueyuan Press, Beijing, China. 319 pp." type="book" year="2000">
Li 
<number box="[1167,1228,655,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); however, at least some of the previous records may refer to one of the below-described new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,728,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce" box="[322,473,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Bruce, A. J. (1982) Notes on some Indo-West Pacific Pontoniinae. XL. The rediscovery of Periclimenes lifuensis Borradaile, 1898 (Decapoda, Pontoniine) and the establishment of its systematic position. Crustaceana, 42, 158 - 173." type="journal article" year="1982">
Bruce (
<number box="[406,465,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
gave the rostral formula for 
<taxonomicName box="[808,944,728,752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerlachei">
<emphasis box="[808,944,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. gerlachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<number box="[986,1028,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
/ 
<number box="[1054,1069,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
. Interestingly, in four examined 
<typeStatus box="[151,238,765,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">syntype</typeStatus>
specimens, the rostral formula is 
<number box="[616,630,764,788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[651,665,764,788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
, which so appears to be the typical rostral formula for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1411,764,788]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="gerlachei">P. gerlachei</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="5" pageNumber="6" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(sensu
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili" box="[270,409,799,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Nobili, G. (1905) Decapodes nouveaux des cotes d'Arabie et du Golfe Persique (diagnoses preliminaires). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 11, 158 - 164." type="journal article" year="1905">
Nobili 
<number box="[349,409,799,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1905.0">1905</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The proportions of the carpus and the palm / fingers ratio of P 
<number box="[1127,1141,799,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
also appear to be variable in 
<taxonomicName box="[180,313,836,860]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerlachei">
<emphasis box="[180,313,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. gerlachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili" box="[327,480,836,860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Nobili, G. (1906) Mission J. Bonnier er Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 90, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 5." type="journal article" year="1906">
Nobili (
<number box="[414,473,836,860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted in the text (p. 
<number box="[714,743,836,860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="47.0">47</number>
) that in some of his specimens, the carpus was proportionally shorter than shown in his figure (
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili" box="[536,1023,871,896]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Nobili, G. (1906) Mission J. Bonnier er Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 90, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 5." type="journal article" year="1906" yearSuffix="a">
Nobili 
<number box="[619,675,871,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1906.0">1906</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[739,769,871,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
a; see also 
<figureCitation box="[897,962,871,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,210,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[169,1417,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philarius gerlachei (Nobili, 1905), syntypes from Persian Gulf (MNHN-Na 1899): A, male, dorsal view; B, ovigerous female, dorsal view; C, same as B, lateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203051/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[951,962,871,895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B
</bibRefCitation>
). Some differences also exist in the armature of the finger cutting edges in P 
<number box="[617,632,908,932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
; for instance, specimens from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1155,908,932]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">China</collectingCountry>
have only two proximal teeth on the dactylus (Li 
<number box="[430,488,943,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2007.0">2007</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[545,590,943,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="153.0">153</number>
e).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName box="[197,416,980,1004]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Philarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerlachei">
<emphasis box="[197,416,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Philarius gerlachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to the four species described below, but can be separated from each of them by a combination of subtle morphological characters summarised in Table 
<number box="[1072,1086,1015,1039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
[see also Remarks under each species below].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
